              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33r0q945/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I had some conversation with <persName>Mr. Isaac\n                                        Hyneman</persName><lb/> to-day, who was one of the persons\n                                        referred to in my<lb/> last, who has been under the same\n                                        impression as<lb/> myself as regards\n                                                  <persName>Ezekiel</persName> having given him\n                                        credit for the<lb/> amount, but says you shall not suffer by\n                                        him &amp; that<lb/> he will pay his account excepting for\n                                        the numbers, which<lb/> he did not receive, amounting to\n                                        about 1 vol. In all. I will<lb/> authorize <persName>Mr. N.\n                                                  Ezekiel</persName> to allow him the amount he<lb/>\n                                        wishes deducted. I will on to-morrow get your matters<lb/>\n                                        out of <persName>Jacob Ezekiels</persName> hands &amp; place\n                                        them with your<lb/> Agent <persName>Mr. N.\n                                                  Ezekiel</persName>, who I hope will make an\n                                        efficient<lb/> one. The next Occidents you forward, he\n                                        wishes you to<lb/> send by Adams Express Serv; direct to\n                                                  <persName>N. Ezekiel</persName> care of<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Jacob A Levy</persName>. I will pay over to him\n                                        the money I owe<lb/> &amp; will endeavour with <persName>Mr.\n                                                  N. E.</persName> to collect all I can<lb/> I have\n                                        nothing of interest to communicate. Our Ball<lb/> in aid of\n                                        the Hebrew School Fund takes place on the<lb/>\n                                        <date>7<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> Feby.</date>\n                                        <persName>Mrs. Myers</persName> the eldest daughter of\n                                                  <persName>Jos. Marx</persName><lb/> deceased died\n                                        here on the <date>17<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> Inst.</p>\n                              <p>Hoping that you are in Health</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">I remain</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">your Friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Isaac A Levy</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>P. S. If you should hear of a suitable person to fill the<lb/>\n                                        office of Hazan, let me hear from you</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33r0q945/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
